## .NET / Visual Studio / VS Code
## Based on GitHub's standard VisualStudio.gitignore, trimmed to what this repo needs.

# User-specific files
*.rsuser
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# User-specific files (MonoDevelop/Xamarin Studio)
*.userprefs

# Generated from web/mesh-monitor by SyncMesh.MeshMonitor.Api's
# BuildFrontend MSBuild target (dotnet publish) — build output, not source.
# The directory itself (wwwroot/.gitkeep) stays tracked: ASP.NET Core's
# WebApplicationBuilder.CreateBuilder() calls UseStaticWebAssets(), which
# constructs a PhysicalFileProvider rooted at wwwroot and throws
# DirectoryNotFoundException at startup if that directory doesn't exist at
# all — before any app code runs, even if nothing under it is ever served.
src/SyncMesh.MeshMonitor.Api/wwwroot/*
!src/SyncMesh.MeshMonitor.Api/wwwroot/.gitkeep

# Local SQLite runtime state (SyncMesh.Daemon's local event buffer, and its
# WAL/shared-memory sidecar files) — never source, always regenerated by
# EF migrations on daemon startup. A previous "*.db" check earlier this
# session was wrong; nothing actually excluded these, and daemon-events.db*
# ended up committed by an auto-checkpoint. Untracking is a separate,
# explicit step — this only stops the bleeding going forward.
daemon-events*.db
daemon-events*.db-shm
daemon-events*.db-wal

